    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-03T09:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-03T09:35:00-05:00" n="580"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d580">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/886: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-03T18:00:00+03:25"
                            >November 3, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1043. My 1037, November 1. Income tax bill has been brought to the floor of the
                    Majlis although debate has not yet begun. I have <pb facs="0565" n="553"
                        xml:id="pg_553"/> received the warmest assurances from Shah and Prime and
                    Foreign Ministers that the bill will pass the Majlis without delay. Therefore
                    both Millspaugh and I feel I am now justified in departing for the United States
                    on leave. I shall take advantage of the delay which has occurred in the arrival
                    at Tehran of the Secretary’s party and proceed with them to the United
                        States.<note n="65" xml:id="d580fn65">Regarding the Minister’s departure for
                        the United States and his return to Tehran, see his telegrams No. 1045,
                        November 4, 9 a.m., and No. 1059, November 13, 9 a.m., <ref target="#pg_400"
                            >pp. 400</ref> and <ref target="#pg_410">410</ref>, respectively.</note>
                    Please hold my mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
